    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-01-03T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-01-03T14:00:00-05:00" n="972"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d972">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">819.00 Revolutions/19: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Panama</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Davis</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-01-03T14:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 3, 1931—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2. Your 9, January 2, 10 p.m. In view of the overthrow of the Panaman Government
                    the Department feels that this Government cannot be called upon to allow
                    transportation of troops across the Canal Zone or to Colon via the Panama
                    Railroad as a matter of right under Article 19 of the Treaty of 1903.<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d972fn3">
                        <ref target="frus1904#pg_543">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1904, p. 543</ref>.</note> The
                    Department leaves to your discretion the granting of such right of transit to
                    the <hi rend="italic">de facto</hi> authorities for purposes of pacification but
                    you should not grant such requests if to do so would lead to fighting in the
                    Canal Zone or the cities of Panama and Colon.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
